'''Robin François Philippe Risser''' (born 2 December 2004) is a French professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{French football updater|Lens}} club [[RC Lens|Lens]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

==Early career==
Born in [[Colmar]], Risser began his youth career at FC Bennwihr. He moved to [[SR Colmar]] in 2015 before joining [[RC Strasbourg|Strasbourg]] in 2017.<ref name="rcs1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.rcstrasbourgalsace.fr/joueurs/robin-risser/|publisher=[[RC Strasbourg]]|access-date=6 March 2024|title=Robin Risser 40|language=fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
Risser was promoted to the first team of [[RC Strasbourg|Strasbourg]] for the [[2022–23 Ligue 2]] season, being the third choice goalkeeper.<ref name="rcs1"/>

On 7 July 2023, Risser joined [[Championnat National]] side [[Dijon FCO|Dijon]] in a one-season loan deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfco.fr/robin-risser-prete-par-strasbourg-au-dfco/|publisher=[[Dijon FCO]]|date=7 July 2023|title=ROBIN RISSER PRÊTÉ PAR STRASBOURG AU DFCO !|language=fr}}</ref> He was chosen to be the first choice keeper of the team for the entire season. On 11 August 2023, he made his debut in the first league match of the season, keeping a clean sheet in a goalless draw against [[FC Rouen 1899|Rouen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bienpublic.com/sport/2023/08/22/dfco-robin-risser-l-heritier|title=Football - National. Robin Risser, l'héritier, gardien de la DFCO|publisher=France Bleu|date=22 August 2023|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dna.fr/education/2023/11/22/robin-risser-un-espoir-du-football-alsacien|title=Journaliste d'un jour. Robin Risser, un espoir du football alsacien|publisher=DNA|date=22 November 2023|language=fr}}</ref>

On 28 November 2024, Risser joins [[Ligue 2]] club [[Red Star FC|Red Star]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://frenchfootballweekly.com/2024/11/28/strasbourg-begins-its-transfer-window-an-announced-transfer/|title=Strasbourg begins its transfer window! An announced transfer|publisher=French Football Weekly}}</ref>

On 4 July 2025, Risser was transferred to [[Ligue 1]] team [[RC Lens|Lens]], signing a contract with the team until June 2030.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rclens.fr/fr/news/robin-risser-rclens-signature-mercato-20250704|title=Robin Risser : dernier rempart, première recrue|publisher=RC Lens|date=4 July 2025|language=fr}}</ref> As Lens' starter goalkeeper, Risser played an important role helping the team finish second in the [[2025–26 Ligue 1]]. As the result, he was given the [[Trophées UNFP du football#Goalkeeper of the Year|Goalkeeper of the Year]] award by UNFP and featured in Ligue 1 Team of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Robin-risser-elu-meilleur-gardien-de-ligue-1-lors-des-trophees-unfp/1675076|title=Robin Risser élu meilleur gardien de Ligue 1 lors des Trophées UNFP|publisher=L'Équipe|date=11 May 2026|language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Risser represented [[France national football team|France]] in several youth categories, including [[France national under-16 football team|France U16]], [[France national under-18 football team|France U18]] and [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://reportersincredules.fr/en-attendant-robin-risser/|title=En attendant... Robin Risser|publisher=Les Reporters Incrédules|date=30 November 2023|language=fr}}</ref> In August 2023, he received his first call up with the [[France national under-21 football team|France national under-21s]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.francebleu.fr/sports/football/le-gardien-du-dfco-robin-risser-appele-avec-l-equipe-de-france-espoirs-9121253|publisher=France Bleu|date=31 August 2023|title=Le gardien du DFCO, Robin Risser, appelé avec l'Equipe de France Espoirs|language=fr}}</ref> On 26 June 2024, he withdrew from the French squad for the [[2024 Summer Olympics]] due to an elbow injury and was replaced by [[Théo De Percin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=RISSER FORFAIT, DE PERCIN CONVOQUÉ|trans-title=Risser forfeited, De Percin called up|language=fr|url=https://www.fff.fr/article/12785-risser-forfait-de-percin-convoque.html|publisher=[[French Football Federation]]|date=26 June 2024}}</ref>

On 14 May 2026, Risser received his first call-up to the [[France national football team|France national team]], being named in the 26-men squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New Zealand Squad Named for FIFA World Cup 2026|url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/165753?newsfeedId=1841052|publisher=[[New Zealand Football]]|date=14 May 2026|access-date=14 May 2026}}</ref>

